snippet.textDisplay: Your right Matt we Canadians do build differently. For example you would not have seen a flat roof almost anywhere in Canada on a house. Our roofs tend to have higher slopes for better snow removal. We also have basements in most of our homes as we have to have foundations that are much deeper to be below the frost level than you need in Texas.  I'm sure there are plenty more things different but I'm also sure if you go to Michigan and New York for example that our houses in Ontario, are built very similar to theirs.
